wib:featureValueObservation.note:
"The future marker in ʕAmmānī Arabic is most often raḥ ˜ rāyiḥ;
                 ḥa- is also used but less frequently. The verb bidd ‘to want’ can also be used as a future marker,
                 with or without ‘volition’ being implied, biddi ʔarūḥ bukra ‘I will go tomorrow’." (Al-Wer 2007:13)

